727413f-b.title: Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - Flushing Avenue
727413f-b.text:
Netropolitan Avenue, (foreground, tracks thereon), between
Flushing Avenue (left) and 53rd Street (right, not shown), showing
at the right hear views of homes on the last mentioned Street. At
the left is a small home on the north side of the second mentioned
Avenue. At the intersection of the aforementioned Avenues, in 1852,
stood a tollgate. This area was once known, as Oceanville. This
is a set of two views.
1922
Views 1 and 2
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
